{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id77b07ca1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7a–2"},"text":"§ 7a–2.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rights, authorities, and liabilities not affected","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in sections 7a to 7a–3 of this title shall be construed to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77b07ca2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–2/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" affect the rights of the Antitrust Division to seek a stay or protective order in a civil action based on conduct covered by an antitrust leniency agreement to prevent the cooperation described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–1/b"},"text":"section 7a–1(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" from impairing or impeding the investigation or prosecution by the Antitrust Division of conduct covered by the agreement;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77b07ca3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–2/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" create any right to challenge any decision by the Antitrust Division with respect to an antitrust leniency agreement; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77b07ca4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–2/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" affect, in any way, the joint and several liability of any party to a civil action described in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–1/a"},"text":"section 7a–1(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":", other than that of the antitrust leniency applicant and cooperating individuals as provided in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–1/a"},"text":"section 7a–1(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id77b07ca5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/237/tII/s214"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–237, title II, § 214","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-06-22"},"text":"June 22, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/667"},"text":"118 Stat. 667","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/190/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–190, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-06-09"},"text":"June 9, 2010","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/124/1276"},"text":"124 Stat. 1276","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id77b07ca6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id77b07ca7-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id77b07ca8-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 7a to 7a–3 of this title, referred to in text, was in the original “this subtitle”, meaning subtitle A (§§ 211–216) of title II of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/237"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–237","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-06-22"},"text":"June 22, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/666"},"text":"118 Stat. 666","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this section and sections 7a, 7a–1, and 7a–3 of this title, amended sections 1, 2, and 3 of this title, and enacted provisions formerly set out in a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":". For complete classification of subtitle A to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id77b07ca9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly set out in a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":", prior to transfer to this section upon repeal of sunset provision."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id77b07caa-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/190/s4/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–190, § 4(1)","children":[],"tail":", made technical amendment to reference in original act which appears in text as reference to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–1/b"},"text":"section 7a–1(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/190/s4/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–190, § 4(2)","children":[],"tail":", made technical amendment to references in original act which appear in two places in text as references to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s7a–1/a"},"text":"section 7a–1(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
